        correct: 2,
        explanation: "Assume $2+\\sqrt{7} = p/q$ (rational). Then $\\sqrt{7} = p/q - 2$, which means $\\sqrt{7}$ is rational. This contradicts the given fact, proving $2+\\sqrt{7}$ is irrational."
